978
01:15:44,957 --> 01:15:46,250
[GURGLING]

979
01:15:58,137 --> 01:16:00,014
- I filled them all in.
- Alright, great.

980
01:16:00,389 --> 01:16:02,266
Now I suggest you send them
all back to their kids

981
01:16:02,475 --> 01:16:04,477
to make sure
everyone stays inside.

982
01:16:04,685 --> 01:16:07,104
- Angela and Judy are missing.
- Oh, no.

983
01:16:07,313 --> 01:16:08,898
- What's all the fuss?
- There's a killer loose.

984
01:16:09,106 --> 01:16:10,983
Make sure no one leaves
your bunk for any reason.

985
01:16:11,358 --> 01:16:12,693
Paul and Ricky
haven't come back yet.

986
01:16:12,902 --> 01:16:14,028
We'd better go look
for them right now.

987
01:16:14,236 --> 01:16:15,237
Everybody out in pairs.

988
01:16:15,446 --> 01:16:17,573
Look everywhere you can think of,
even the empty cabins.

989
01:16:17,948 --> 01:16:19,742
Let me get my flashlight.

990
01:16:42,056 --> 01:16:43,390
I didn't think
you were gonna show.

991
01:16:47,520 --> 01:16:49,522
- Let's go swimming.
- Now?

992
01:16:50,356 --> 01:16:53,275
- What about our clothes?
- Take them off.

993
01:16:54,819 --> 01:16:55,820
Okay!

994
01:17:35,359 --> 01:17:36,443
Found one.

995
01:17:39,196 --> 01:17:40,281
Ricky.

996
01:17:43,784 --> 01:17:45,619
[COUGHING]

997
01:17:45,870 --> 01:17:46,829
Hey, he's alive!

998
01:17:47,621 --> 01:17:48,497
[WHEEZING]

999
01:17:55,671 --> 01:17:58,257
[SCREAMING]

1000
01:18:03,470 --> 01:18:04,597
It's Meg.

1001
01:18:05,055 --> 01:18:07,057
It's so horrible!

1002
01:18:07,266 --> 01:18:10,311
[SOBBING]

1003
01:18:31,832 --> 01:18:33,042
Angela!

1004
01:18:33,584 --> 01:18:34,668
Judy!

1005
01:18:35,169 --> 01:18:37,922
Ricky, Paul!
You guys out here?

1006
01:18:39,632 --> 01:18:41,008
Hey.
You hear something?

1007
01:18:42,092 --> 01:18:43,844
- What?
- Listen.

1008
01:18:44,970 --> 01:18:46,430
Sounds like singing.

1009
01:18:48,599 --> 01:18:51,393
Damn it.
It's coming from over here.

1010
01:18:56,190 --> 01:18:58,484
[OFF-KEY HUMMING]

1011
01:18:59,193 --> 01:19:00,236
It's Angela!

1012
01:19:01,070 --> 01:19:03,364
Angela! Are you alright?
<i> </i>

1013
01:19:04,990 --> 01:19:07,701
Angela! Are you okay?

1014
01:19:09,119 --> 01:19:10,621
Angela,
can you hear me?

1015
01:19:18,087 --> 01:19:20,923
Oh, you're going to enjoy
living with us so much!

1016
01:19:21,131 --> 01:19:22,549
Yes, I know you are.

1017
01:19:22,758 --> 01:19:26,553
As a welcome-home present I bought
you such wonderful new clothes.

1018
01:19:26,887 --> 01:19:28,472
I just hope that Richard
doesn't get jealous

1019
01:19:28,681 --> 01:19:30,432
that I didn't get
him anything.

1020
01:19:30,641 --> 01:19:34,645
Oh, but then he is such a dear.
I'm sure that he won't mind.

1021
01:19:35,062 --> 01:19:37,606
You see,
I've always wanted a little girl.

1022
01:19:37,982 --> 01:19:40,442
But of course,
when my husband left...

1023
01:19:40,693 --> 01:19:41,694
Oh, well!

1024
01:19:41,902 --> 01:19:44,405
That's all water under
the bridge, as I always say.

1025
01:19:44,613 --> 01:19:46,407
Water under the bridge.

1026
01:19:46,615 --> 01:19:49,952
But it certainly will be a nice little
surprise when Richard comes home

1027
01:19:50,160 --> 01:19:51,787
to find a little girl in the house.

1028
01:19:52,579 --> 01:19:57,543
Yes, I've always dreamed
of a little girl just like you.

1029
01:19:58,168 --> 01:20:00,170
I mean,
we already have a boy.

1030
01:20:00,379 --> 01:20:05,050
So another one simply would not do.
Oh, no, absolutely not.

1031
01:20:05,259 --> 01:20:09,346
A little girl would be so much nicer.
Don't you think so, Angela?

1032
01:20:10,180 --> 01:20:11,724
Angela...

1033
01:20:11,932 --> 01:20:13,767
Such a lovely name.

1034
01:20:15,185 --> 01:20:17,062
Why, I believe it means "angel."

1035
01:20:17,271 --> 01:20:19,231
Why, yes.
I'm sure it does.

1036
01:20:19,440 --> 01:20:21,525
I know you're going
to like that name.

1037
01:20:21,734 --> 01:20:23,736
Won't you, Peter?

1038
01:20:24,194 --> 01:20:27,990
[SNARLING]

1039
01:20:28,949 --> 01:20:30,492
How can it be?

1040
01:20:30,701 --> 01:20:33,662
[SNARLING]

1041
01:20:36,165 --> 01:20:37,750
My God, she's a boy.

